                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60p2/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-24T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1927—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Your 16, February 21, 4 p.m. Department has no objection to including in
                    Article 16 the last paragraph of Article 7 of draft and the first eleven lines
                    of last paragraph of Article 7 of United States-German Treaty.</p>
                <p>Please submit proposed text to Department before final agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
